Interface BaseImages

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseImagesTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseImagesStub

    public interface BaseImages
extends Service, BaseImagesTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The BaseImages interface provides methods to manage trusted instances of ESX software on a cluster level. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

    • Method Detail

      • importFromImgdb

        BaseImages.ImportFromImgdbInvocation importFromImgdb(java.lang.String cluster,
                                                     byte[] imgdb)
        Import ESX metadata as a new trusted base image to each host in the cluster.

        Import a boot_imgdb.tgz file which contains metadata that describes a trusted ESX base image. A boot_imgdb.tgz file can be downloaded from a representative host.

        . This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        The imported imgdb version identifier. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.trust_authority_clusters.attestation.os.esx.BaseImage.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The id of the cluster on which the operation will be executed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        imgdb - ESX metadata on a cluster level.
        Returns:
        instance of BaseImages.ImportFromImgdbInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described importFromImgdb operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        AlreadyExists - if ESX metadata for the same version has already been added.
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        InvalidArgument - if the imgdb is invalid or cluster id is empty.
        NotFound - if the cluster is not found.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.
